pletely consistent.  All you've done is point out a mistake on my part that has nothing to do with the arguement at hand.<br>
<br>
So how am I a hypocrite, and how am I lacking &quot;moral backbone&quot;?  I stated that if you break Verant's rules, you should take responsibility for the consequences.  I've stated that the name Arikel (and only the name, not the character from the Vampire game) is not covered by copyright law, as stated by Congress itself.  I've stated that you don't know what the hell you're talking about.  None of those things make me a hypocrite.  Hell, you've started this thread saying you don't take things said on an Internet BB seriously.  Now you're bringing up the rather serious issue of morality.  By your own standards (that is, that one is not allowed to change one's mind, discover new information, or forget about a couple irrelevant posts from a gimpy necro whine thread), you have in fact proven yourself to be a hypocrite. <p>Arikel, n00b thane of The Grey Legion <BR>
